The Store Corporation Bhd., a
Malaysian operator of department stores, supermarkets and
hypermarkets, borrowed 300 million ringgit, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  One 240 million ringgit facility matures in 2019 and the 60
million ringgit balance in 2017, the data show.  Hong Leong Bank
Bhd. (HLBK)  and HSBC Holdings Plc provided the funds, which will be
used to refinance debt and for working capital, the data show.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Katrina Nicholas at 
